# Folder Structure Enforcement

Follow the template in `FOLDER_STRUCTURE.md` for all structural decisions.

## Agent Packages

When adding a new agent, create `src/<agent_name>/` with these subfolders:

```
src/<agent_name>/
├── __init__.py
├── <agent_name>.py        # Graph entry point (compiled graph export)
├── graph_builder.py       # Graph construction (nodes, edges, conditionals)
├── configuration.py       # Runtime configuration
├── settings.py            # Agent-level env vars
├── nodes/                 # One file per node or group of related nodes
├── prompts/               # Prompt templates separated by task
├── schemas/               # TypedDict / Pydantic state and data models
└── tools/                 # @tool functions + get_tools() assembly
```

## Placement Rules

- New graph nodes go in `<agent>/nodes/` -- never in `graph_builder.py`.
- New prompt templates go in `<agent>/prompts/` -- never inline in node code.
- New data models go in `<agent>/schemas/` -- never defined inside nodes.
- Taxonomy/enum values go only in `taxonomy.py` (single source of truth).
- Shared integrations (used by 2+ agents) go in `src/services/<name>/`.
- Agent-specific tools stay in `<agent>/tools/`.
- No business logic in `__init__.py` files -- only re-exports.

## Registering a New Agent

1. Export compiled graph from `<agent_name>.py`.
2. Register in `langgraph.json` under `"graphs"`.
3. Add tests in `tests/`.
4. Update docs in `docs/`.
